Jeff Wicks, News24Ballito protest (IPSS Medical Rescue, Supplied to News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Violent protest action has closed the N2 and other arterial roads that surround the informal settlement of Shaka's Head near Ballito on Tuesday morning.- Are you there? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos. IPSS spokesperson Paul Herbst said protesters had taken to the bridge that runs over the N2 and had stoned passing cars.&ldquo;At this stage the N2 has been closed while police deal with the situation,&rdquo; he said.Herbst added that the P445, a link road between Ballito and Compensation, had also been closed by the angry rioters who had erected burning blockades across the carriageway.The action is understood to relate to the choice of an ANC ward councillor candidate in the area.In February, residents took to the street and ran riot in Ballito, setting fire to the councillor Jetro Banda&rsquo;s car and house.He had to be taken to a place of safety until the backlash had subsided.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.